\begin_layout Plain Layout
$^1$The index of labor-intensive seed handling practices contains 6 variables:
 whether seed is stored in dedicated area,
 in correct lighting,
 on correct surface,
 not in open containers,
 whether shop has no pest problem,
 cleanness and professionality rating by enumerator.
\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
$^2$The index of capital-intensive seed handling practices contains 5 variables:
 whether roof is leak-proof,
 roof is insulated,
 walls are insulated,
 shop is ventilated,
 expired seed is handled correctly.
 All variables were observed or verified by enumerators,
 except the last,
 which is self-reported.
\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
$^3$The index of services (self-reported) contains 8 variables:
 whether shop offers explanations,
 complementary input recommendations,
 extension/training,
 discounts for larger quantities,
 credit,
 did not receive seed related customer complaint,
 accepts mobile money,
 stocks small (not repackaged) seed package.
\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
$^4$The index of services (reported by farmers) contains 7 variables:
 whether shop offers refund/insurance,
 credit,
 training/advice,
 delivery,
 after-sales service,
 accepts different payment methods,
 sells small quantities.
 Farmers’ responses are aggregated at dealer level,
 then the index is computed.
\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
$^5$The index of quality signaling practices includes 5 variables:
 whether shop displays official certificate,
 is registered with UNADA,
 is a member of another professional association,
 holds a trading license issued by local government,
 number of shop inspections.
