\begin_layout Subsection
Alternative index construction
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "robustness"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We recompute all summary indices following 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "kling2007experimental"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 as a robustness check to the 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "anderson2008multiple"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 indices used in the main analysis.
 For farmers’ perceptions of seed performance,
 the treatment effect becomes statistically insignificant when the index is constructed following 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "kling2007experimental"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Results for farmers’ adoption and sourcing decisions remain robust.
 Results for agro-dealers’ business activity (general,
 Longe 10H,
 and Longe 5) are largely robust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For farmers’ harvest outcomes,
 the positive endline effect remains robust.
 At midline,
 however,
 the 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "kling2007experimental"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 index yields a significant negative coefficient.
 The harvest outcomes included in the index are mechanically related (e.g.,
 yield,
 production,
 and revenue).
 The 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "anderson2008multiple"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 method down-weights highly correlated components,
 whereas 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "kling2007experimental"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 assigns equal weights and treats these outcomes as independent,
 which can amplify the influence of redundant information and generate a negative treatment effect.
 That is why we rely on the 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "anderson2008multiple"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 method,
 as pre-registered in our 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "pre-analysis plan"
target "https://www.socialscienceregistry.org/trials/6361"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 and use 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "kling2007experimental"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 only as a robustness check.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Results for agro-dealers’ practices remain robust,
 as do all null results regarding agro-dealers’ seed performance.
\end_layout

